  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support Poor Roma Families in Savra Community with Jersey Cows</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will be implemented within the Roma community in Savra village of Lushnja region. The objective of this project is to improve the nutrition and income of 20 poor Roma farmers&#x2019; families (10 original and 10 POG) in Savra community and help their integration into the community. Ten pregnant Jersey heifers will be distributed to 10 Roma farmers&#x2019; families. In addition, 10 other farmers&#x2019; families will benefit from Pass on the Gift. The Jersey heifers will be purchased in the local market. The beneficiary families will be supported with trainings, technical assistance and agriculture supplies. The project will contribute to reducing poverty, improving economic and social status, as well as improving their integration in the community.</narrative>
  </description>
